        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`ForbidPrimitiveInTypes` does not scan `WherePredicateDecl.lhs`. The spec includes primitive detection for configured positions where `TypeRef` appears generally, and `where` left-hand sides are explicitly TypeRef expressions, e.g. `where Vec<String>: Clone`. This collector only pushes generic bounds and `pred.rhs`, so a `Bound`/`String` rule, and even nested `ResultErr` in the lhs, silently misses primitive occurrences in `pred.lhs`. Add the lhs as a `PrimitiveOccurrencePosition::Bound` slot before scanning the rhs bounds.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/domain/src/tddd/catalogue_linter_eval_primitives.rs",
              "line": 283,
              "category": "primitive obsession"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:6538b6e7165110f7ad5ec25a82fa9bba024059c92310e348a8d5c76487698729",
          "at": "2026-07-02T01:35:46Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:be1eefe97724e4db9269aed86cae4a05ff6600d24a2f3e2745f46a1a94975ee2",
          "at": "2026-07-02T02:04:03Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`evaluate_forbid_primitive_in_types` only checks whether the current `target_layer_id` is present in `layers` and otherwise returns `Ok(Vec::new())`. It never validates the rest of `layers` against `all_catalogues`, so a typo or removed layer in the rule can be silently ignored and the lint fails open for that layer. This should surface `UnknownLayer` for any missing configured layer before returning.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/domain/src/tddd/catalogue_linter_eval_primitives.rs",
              "line": 78,
              "category": "missing error handling"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:4f6dbfa3269b439f127c480844d9414ab891937b1ddf29a949b2f7fa91400209",
          "at": "2026-07-02T03:18:54Z"
