          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:6919b88332b2ae604276667d93a8a856b9c8c68db3a1d3aaed8166992716b429",
          "at": "2026-07-02T04:13:51Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The new `include_bound` gate skips every catalogue Bound slot unless `Bound` itself is requested. That also skips scan-intrinsic positions discovered inside those bounds, especially `ResultErr`: with the default `positions=[result_err]` rule, a valid bound such as `T: Into<Result<(), String>>` is never passed to the scanner, so the raw `String` error type is accepted even though `ResultErr` is explicitly enforced globally. This weakens the primitive-obsession invariant; the filter needs to preserve bound slots when any requested position can be found by scanning inside a bound, or handle bound parsing without dropping `ResultErr` coverage.",
